<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>Trump Cancels Signing of Executive Order Granting Oversight of A.I. Models</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/technology/trump-ai-executive-order.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/technology/trump-ai-executive-order.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/technology/trump-ai-executive-order.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The president said he postponed the executive order, which would give the government power to evaluate A.I. models before their release, over concerns about “aspects of it.”</description><dc:creator>Tripp Mickle and Sheera Frenkel</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 14:53:31 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Executive Orders</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/21/multimedia/21biz-ai-trump-eo-sub-lqbp/21biz-ai-trump-eo-sub-lqbp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Doug Mills/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>On Wednesday President Trump invited A.I. chief executives to Thursday’s signing event, but many could not make it in time.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Bluesky Says Kremlin Is Hacking Its Platform to Spread Propaganda</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/business/bluesky-russia-hacking-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/business/bluesky-russia-hacking-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/21/business/bluesky-russia-hacking-accounts.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company said it was fighting Russian efforts to hijack real users’ accounts to post fake content, an apparently novel tactic.</description><dc:creator>Steven Lee Myers</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 09:02:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Bluesky</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Russia</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Propaganda</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Foreign Policy</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Russian Invasion of Ukraine (2022)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Rumors and Misinformation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/18/business/00Bluesky-Disinfo/00Bluesky-Disinfo-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Davide Bonaldo/Sipa USA, via Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>Russia hacked into the accounts of real people on Bluesky to spread fake articles, the social media platform said. </media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>